Practiced making simple project like:
* Word-breakdown-app

math - is a built in module that can help us make complex mathematical functions
input() - let us type
int() - let us transform strings to integers or float to integers
float() - let us transform strings to float or integers to float
bool() - basically sees everything that has NONE a false and if there is something inside the string it will return a True, this also works in integers and float if the number is larger or smaller than 0 its a true but if it 0 its a false
> - greater than will check if the number or string on the left is larger than the right
< - less than will check if the number or string of the left is smaller than the right
>= - greater than or equal to, checks if the number or strings on the left is larger than the right or if its equal
<= - less than or equal to, checks if the number or strings on the left is smaller than the right or if its equal
!= - checks if the number or strings is different
CONDITIONAL STATEMENTS
if - let us make conditions
elif - we usually use this whenever we want to make multiple conditions
else - if none of the conditions work this will be the only one to be printed out

