for - use to make loops or print the same thing over and over again
range() - where we put how many times, something will run  in a loop you can put how long you wanted it to be inside the loop (3), (1, 4)
number - a built in int variable usually use to track and count how many times tou will run a loop
iterable - something you can loop through
uniterable - something you can't loop through
mutable - you can change it after creating it
immutable - you cant change it after creating it
while - is a type of loop like the for loop with the only difference of that for loops, loop a specific numbe of times depending on what you put in the range() meanwhile a while loop continues to loop till the condition becomes False
def - a function, doesnt take any input like print()
return - as the same suggest it returns a function inside back

