tuple - you cant change whatever you put inside, a tuple is a parethesis (), immutable and works almost like a list, for example (2.5, 1.5, 3.3)
list - you can change, add, remove anything you put inside, a tuple is a square bracket [], and can store multiple data, for example ["Niko", "Maureen", "Aron"]
set - cannot contain duplicate, a dictionary is a curly bracket {} for example, {1, 2, 3, 4, 5}
dictionary - we can add multiple datas with there own value like {'bob': 1, 'James': 2}

